The paper discusses incorporating prior knowledge into Bayesian models for data streams, which is a problem that falls under the umbrella of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of external knowledge sources such as ontologies and Wikipedia suggests a potential connection to databases (cs.DB). The sequential nature of the data and the focus on time-series models suggest a possible connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the use of Bayesian models for text classification suggests a potential connection to information retrieval (cs.IR).
